snippet.textDisplay: Idea for one of the next Pass it on challenges: pair cooking. So establish the order, then make the guys cook in pairs: 1 and 2, pass it to 3 and 4, then 5 and 1, 2 and 3 and finally, 4 and 5. Even though this will mean one person will participate both in rounds 1 and 3, relatively close to each other, I think, the overall mess in doing it this way will make it fun. And this will allow them to actually make some plans, oven, fridge and microwave. Or even do it the "remote controlled" way, the same order.

The end was the best bit 😁
I think I don't envy James and Ben having to judge, as all 3 dishes looked really good and there was so little in the way of criticism for any of them. But Jamie should still go last because he said Panne is French but let's pretend it's Japanese... when CREOLE is French based, so it tied in that way. Mike's looked delicious, and Barry had the most creative one, imo.
